<subSubSection id="C3246521FFE5FF8632B7FA628F86FE61" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="537" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" type="key">
<key id="FFAF619BFFE5FF8632B7FA628F86FE61" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="537" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<keyStep id="30CA2E0FFFE5FF9932B7FA628F86F997" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<paragraph id="8B8136AAFFE5FF9932B7FA628F87FA59" blockId="15.[151,1437,1430,2042]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="30CF959FFFE5FF9932B7FA628F87FA59" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
1. Proboscis at repose surpassing posterior coxa. Clypeus strongly protuberant, clypeocular distance 0.72–0.96 times 
<collectionCode id="ED2FAE6FFFE5FF993713FA628F74FA7F" box="[1331,1390,1463,1484]" country="Italy" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" name="University of Modena and Reggio Emilia, Department of Biology" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" type="University or college">MOD</collectionCode>
. Hypostomal carina with strong, anterior spiniform projection (
<figureCitation id="13052A2FFFE5FF99313CFA018968FA58" box="[796,882,1492,1515]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1288,1312]" captionTargetBox="[215,1371,372,1262]" captionTargetId="figure-289@15.[215,1371,372,1262]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 12. A–B, dorsal view of female pronotal lobe (p, pronotal lobe). A, A. bonariensis Brèthes. B, A. mesopotamica (Holmberg). C–D, lateral view of male head showing hypostomal carina (h). C, A. halictoides (Holmberg). D, A. bonariensis Brèthes. Scale lines = A–D, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4897164" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4897164/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Fig. 12C</figureCitation>
)................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D29FFE5FF993736FA018F87FA59" authority="Holmberg, 1903" authorityName="Holmberg" authorityYear="1903" box="[1302,1437,1492,1514]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Leptergatis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halictoides">
<emphasis id="B94AEAB8FFE5FF993736FA018F87FA59" bold="true" box="[1302,1437,1492,1514]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">A. halictoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136AAFFE5FF9932B7FA278F86F997" blockId="15.[151,1437,1430,2042]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="30CF959FFFE5FF9932B7FA278F86F997" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
- Proboscis at repose barely surpassing anterior coxa. Clypeus less protuberant, clypeocular distance 0.3 times 
<collectionCode id="ED2FAE6FFFE5FF993736FA278F54F9B4" box="[1302,1358,1522,1543]" country="Italy" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" name="University of Modena and Reggio Emilia, Department of Biology" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" type="University or college">MOD</collectionCode>
or less. Hypostomal carina anteriorly at most with rounded elevation (
<figureCitation id="13052A2FFFE5FF993118F9DA8994F996" box="[824,910,1551,1573]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1288,1312]" captionTargetBox="[215,1371,372,1262]" captionTargetId="figure-289@15.[215,1371,372,1262]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 12. A–B, dorsal view of female pronotal lobe (p, pronotal lobe). A, A. bonariensis Brèthes. B, A. mesopotamica (Holmberg). C–D, lateral view of male head showing hypostomal carina (h). C, A. halictoides (Holmberg). D, A. bonariensis Brèthes. Scale lines = A–D, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4897164" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4897164/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Fig. 12D</figureCitation>
)......................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30CA2E0FFFE5FF9932B7F9F88F86F9D3" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<paragraph id="8B8136AAFFE5FF9932B7F9F88F86F9F1" blockId="15.[151,1437,1430,2042]" box="[151,1436,1580,1602]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="30CF959FFFE5FF9932B7F9F88F86F9F1" box="[151,1436,1580,1602]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">2. First and second segments of labial palpus with modified, hooked setae.......................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136AAFFE5FF9932B7F99F8F86F9D3" blockId="15.[151,1437,1430,2042]" box="[151,1436,1610,1632]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="30CF959FFFE5FF9932B7F99F8F86F9D3" box="[151,1436,1610,1632]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">- First and second segments of labial palpus with simple setae, not hooked. …...................................... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30CA2E0FFFE5FF9932B7F9B28F86F8F9" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<paragraph id="8B8136AAFFE5FF9932B7F9B28F87F966" blockId="15.[151,1437,1430,2042]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="30CF959FFFE5FF9932B7F9B28F87F966" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
3. Scape without yellow mark (
<figureCitation id="13052A2FFFE5FF9933D4F9B2885BF9CE" box="[500,577,1639,1661]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,956,1948]" captionTargetId="figure-392@7.[154,1434,956,1948]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Males, A. ursinus species group, head, frontal view. A, A. bonariensis Brèthes. B, A. halictoides (Holmberg). C, A. holmbergi sp. n. D, A. mesopotamica (Holmberg). Scale lines = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4897140" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4897140/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Ventral part of mesopleuron without projection in front of mid coxa. Posterior basitarsus with rounded apex (
<figureCitation id="13052A2FFFE5FF993382F9518BE6F928" box="[418,508,1668,1691]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,1035,1952]" captionTargetId="figure-205@13.[201,1387,1035,1952]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 10. Males, A. ursinus species group, posterior basitarsus, ventral view. A, A. bonariensis Brèthes. B, A. halictoides (Holmberg). C, A. holmbergi sp. n. D, A. mesopotamica (Holmberg). Scale lines = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4897160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4897160/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
). Posterior tibia with under surface nearly glabrous and ventral inner margin with tubercule continued apically by carina up to tibial spur. 
<collectionCode id="ED2FAE6FFFE5FF99304FF9778864F90B" box="[623,638,1698,1720]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">T</collectionCode>
3– 
<collectionCode id="ED2FAE6FFFE5FF9930B6F97788BFF90B" box="[662,677,1698,1720]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">T</collectionCode>
5 with brownish hairs on discs and distinct white to yellowish apical bands (
<figureCitation id="13052A2FFFE5FF993755F9778B1BF966" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1197,1221]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1173]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[154,1434,181,1173]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Males, A. ursinus species group, lateral view. A, A. bonariensis Brèthes. B, A. halictoides (Holmberg). C, A. holmbergi sp. n. D, A. mesopotamica (Holmberg). Scale line= A, C and D, 0.1 mm; B, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4897134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4897134/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
)..................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D29FFE5FF99372EF96A8F87F966" box="[1294,1437,1727,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Ancyloscelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bonariensis">
<emphasis id="B94AEAB8FFE5FF99372EF96A8F87F966" bold="true" box="[1294,1437,1727,1749]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">A. bonariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136AAFFE5FF9932B7F9088F86F8F9" blockId="15.[151,1437,1430,2042]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="30CF959FFFE5FF9932B7F9088F86F8F9" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
- Scape with yellow mark (
<figureCitation id="13052A2FFFE5FF9933F9F909883FF940" box="[473,549,1756,1779]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,956,1948]" captionTargetId="figure-392@7.[154,1434,956,1948]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Males, A. ursinus species group, head, frontal view. A, A. bonariensis Brèthes. B, A. halictoides (Holmberg). C, A. holmbergi sp. n. D, A. mesopotamica (Holmberg). Scale lines = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4897140" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4897140/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). Ventral part of mesopleuron with projection in front of mid coxa. Posterior basitarsus with pointed apex (
<figureCitation id="13052A2FFFE5FF99334EF92F8BCDF8A3" box="[366,471,1786,1808]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,956,1948]" captionTargetId="figure-392@7.[154,1434,956,1948]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Males, A. ursinus species group, head, frontal view. A, A. bonariensis Brèthes. B, A. halictoides (Holmberg). C, A. holmbergi sp. n. D, A. mesopotamica (Holmberg). Scale lines = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4897140" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4897140/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Fig. 3B–D</figureCitation>
). Posterior tibia with under surface densely pilose and ventral inner margin without tubercule nor carina, or with carina medially, not reaching to tibial spur. Discs of 
<collectionCode id="ED2FAE6FFFE5FF99315EF8C28997F89E" box="[894,909,1815,1837]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">T</collectionCode>
2– 
<collectionCode id="ED2FAE6FFFE5FF993186F8C289AFF89E" box="[934,949,1815,1837]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">T</collectionCode>
5 and apical bands with yellow-golden hairs (
<figureCitation id="13052A2FFFE5FF993755F8C28B07F8F8" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1197,1221]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1173]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[154,1434,181,1173]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Males, A. ursinus species group, lateral view. A, A. bonariensis Brèthes. B, A. halictoides (Holmberg). C, A. holmbergi sp. n. D, A. mesopotamica (Holmberg). Scale line= A, C and D, 0.1 mm; B, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4897134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4897134/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Fig. 2C–D</figureCitation>
)............................................................................................. 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30CA2E0FFFE5FF9932B7F8878F86F836" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<paragraph id="8B8136AAFFE5FF9932B7F8878F86F8D4" blockId="15.[151,1437,1430,2042]" box="[151,1436,1874,1896]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="30CF959FFFE5FF9932B7F8878F86F8D4" box="[151,1436,1874,1896]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
4. Posterior basitarsus with inner curved tooth between basal third and middle of basitarsus (
<figureCitation id="13052A2FFFE5FF993662F8878E82F8DB" box="[1090,1176,1874,1896]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,1035,1952]" captionTargetId="figure-205@13.[201,1387,1035,1952]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 10. Males, A. ursinus species group, posterior basitarsus, ventral view. A, A. bonariensis Brèthes. B, A. halictoides (Holmberg). C, A. holmbergi sp. n. D, A. mesopotamica (Holmberg). Scale lines = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4897160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4897160/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
)..... 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D29FFE5FF9936D3F8878F86F8D4" authority="Holmberg, 1903" authorityName="Holmberg" authorityYear="1903" box="[1267,1436,1874,1895]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Leptergatis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesopotamica">
<emphasis id="B94AEAB8FFE5FF9936D3F8878F86F8D4" bold="true" box="[1267,1436,1874,1895]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">A. mesopotamica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136AAFFE5FF9932B7F8A58F86F836" blockId="15.[151,1437,1430,2042]" box="[151,1436,1903,1925]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="30CF959FFFE5FF9932B7F8A58F86F836" box="[151,1436,1903,1925]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
- Posterior basitarsus without inner tooth (
<figureCitation id="13052A2FFFE5FF993048F8BA88D2F837" box="[616,712,1903,1925]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,1035,1952]" captionTargetId="figure-205@13.[201,1387,1035,1952]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 10. Males, A. ursinus species group, posterior basitarsus, ventral view. A, A. bonariensis Brèthes. B, A. halictoides (Holmberg). C, A. holmbergi sp. n. D, A. mesopotamica (Holmberg). Scale lines = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4897160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4897160/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Figs. 10C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A2FFFE5FF9930F3F8BA88EBF836" box="[723,753,1903,1925]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1468,1492]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1018,1445]" captionTargetId="figure-301@9.[151,1435,1018,1445]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Ancyloscelis ursinus, holotype (NHMUK 10265363). A, right posterior basitarsus, lateroventral view. B, ventral view of apex of metasoma. (Photographs, attention of David Notton, Natural History Museum, London). Scale lines = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4897146" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4897146/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">5A</figureCitation>
)...................................................... 5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30CA2E0FFFE5FF9932B7F8598F86F84A" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<paragraph id="8B8136AAFFE5FF9932B7F8598F86F80C" blockId="15.[151,1437,1430,2042]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="30CF959FFFE5FF9932B7F8598F86F80C" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
5. S6 strongly emarginate (
